<br>
I tested (not scientifically, sorry, I am not Dr. Parse nor Prof. Log /bow Cyricus) the upgraded GV Air yesterday in BW doing the Nez spawn point.    [NB - the -500 -2500 tactic works perfectly so you DO NOT need a tracker, and we got 2 BE after 5 hours]<br>
<br>
We had like 14 Nez and 3 Phurzikon pops at the spawn point.<br>
<br>
Because of the many adds (skellies, apes, wasps, etc.) it was frequent for me as I was the highest level in group to start solo on Nez when it spawned, the lower group members taking care of the adds/roamers.<br>
<br>
GV Air tanked wonderful against Nez, even against the higher version (summoning one). I almost soloed one of the Nez before my mates jumped in on a particular add intensive cycle (7 mobs in a row), and pet was at 50%, Nez at 25% (of couse I also nuked, Manastorm works ok against Nez).<br>
<br>
What is very nice is though wurms cannot be stunned, I never gained aggro even when I nuked early, so I tend to guess the stun still generates high aggro, which is always a plus.<br>
<br>
Against the other mobs, pet was able to solo almost everything, including blue conning (for some of them) scoriae hornets.<br>
<br>
Last week, on the same spawn, GV Air was much weaker.<br>
<br>
I also think the hps might have been upgraded.<br>
<br>
What are your thoughts ?<br>
<br>
